<plot>The Assassin is just that. A hired gun, that shows no mercy and methodically does his job with no emotion. When he is contracted to kill a family that includes a child, he seems to not be concerned, until faced with the little boy trembling in the closet. Emotion creeps in, is it enough to stop him from pulling the trigger? Is it ever to late to do what is right? There are no rules in life, just choices.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?282810</url></doc>
